    {\displaystyle \lim _{N\to \infty }\left\|{1 \over N}\sum _{n=0}^{N-1}f\circ T^{n}-\int _{X}f\,d\mu \right\|_{L^{2}(X,\mu )}=0.}
  A dynamical system 
  
    
      
        (
        X
        ,
        
          
            A
          
        
        ,
        μ
        ,
        T
        )
      
    
    {\displaystyle (X,{\mathcal {A}},\mu ,T)}
   is weakly mixing if, for any functions 
  
    
      
