        )
      
    
    {\displaystyle (\Omega ,{\mathcal {F}},\mathbb {P} )}
  . The sequence space into which the process maps can be endowed with a topology, the product topology. The open sets of this topology are called cylinder sets. These cylinder sets generate a σ-algebra, the Borel σ-algebra; this is the smallest σ-algebra that contains the topology.
Define a function 
  
    
      
        α
      
    
    {\displaystyle \alpha }
  , called the strong mixing coefficient, as

  
    
      
