   as 
  
    
      
        s
        →
        ∞
      
    
    {\displaystyle s\to \infty }
  . That is to say, a strongly mixing process is such that, in a way that is uniform over all times 
  
    
      
        t
      
    
    {\displaystyle t}
   and all events, the events before time 
  
    
      
        t
      
    
    {\displaystyle t}
   and the events after time 
  
    
      
